THE FIGHTING RETREAT
The objective is the docking port, not victory. The party must climb the spiral staircase through the archive while Spheres deploy from the walls.
Mechanics: Each round, one character can attempt to ADVANCE (move one "zone" up the staircase — there are 3 zones between the workshop and the docking port). Advancing requires either:
Might TN 12 to shove past a blocking Sphere
Agility TN 12 to dodge around it
A successful attack that Staggers or destroys the blocking enemy
Characters who don't advance can fight, defend, or use abilities to create openings for others.
The staircase viewports: The spiral staircase passes the Blackreach viewports. Through them, the party can see the cavern below — and now, for the first time, they can see MOVEMENT down there. The distant Dwemer structures they saw as dead ruins on the way down are lighting up. Amber lamps flickering to crimson across the underground city. The entire Blackreach installation is waking up. What they are fighting in the Cognitorium is a FRACTION of what is activating below.
GEAR DURING THIS PHASE:
GEAR rolls alongside the party, cheerfully providing commentary.
"Two Spheres approaching from the archive level! Their targeting algorithms are quite sophisticated. I helped design them!"
"Current survival probability updated: 3.8%. A slight decline. How exciting!"
GEAR IN COMBAT: He is a party NPC. He can take actions.
